edu.lehigh.cse.lol

Class Goodie

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.lehigh.cse.lol.BaseActor
      • edu.lehigh.cse.lol.WorldActor
        • edu.lehigh.cse.lol.Goodie

  • public class Goodie
extends WorldActor
    Goodies are actors that a hero can collect.

    Collecting a goodie has three possible consequences: it can change the score, it can change the hero's strength, and it can make the hero invincible

      • setScore

        public void setScore(int v1,
                     int v2,
                     int v3,
                     int v4)
        Set the score of this goodie. This indicates how many points the goodie is worth... each value can be positive or negative
        Parameters:
        v1 - The number of points that are added to the 1st score when the goodie is collected
        v2 - The number of points that are added to the 2nd score when the goodie is collected
        v3 - The number of points that are added to the 3rd score when the goodie is collected
        v4 - The number of points that are added to the 4th score when the goodie is collected

      • setStrengthBoost

        public void setStrengthBoost(int boost)
        Indicate how much strength the hero gains by collecting this goodie
        Parameters:
        boost - Amount of strength to add (can be negative)

      • setInvincibilityDuration

        public void setInvincibilityDuration(float duration)
        Indicate how long the hero will be invincible after collecting this goodie
        Parameters:
        duration - Amount of time the hero will be invincible. Note that for a hero who is currently invincible, this value will be /added/ to the hero's remaining invincibility time

      • setEnabled

        public void setEnabled(boolean val)
        Specify whether this Renderable object is enabled or disabled. When it is disabled, it effectively does not exist in the game.
        Parameters:
        val - The new state (true for enabled, false for disabled)
